3
00:00:04,849 --> 00:00:08,416
The Neptune Sheriff's Department has apprehended Abel Koontz… Shoes and a backpack…

4
00:00:08,477 --> 00:00:12,190
The Lilly Kane murder file. Dad still hasn't given up on the case.

5
00:00:12,257 --> 00:00:14,021
We all lost Lilly and we all miss her.

6
00:00:14,083 --> 00:00:16,064
Duncan Kane. He used to be my boyfriend.

7
00:00:16,122 --> 00:00:18,374
I just want to see him passionate about something.

8
00:00:18,445 --> 00:00:20,360
And let's not forget Logan Echolls.

9
00:00:20,432 --> 00:00:24,600
Every school has an obligatory psychotic jackass. He's ours.

10
00:00:24,652 --> 00:00:28,450
You think you're this big outsider, push comes to shove, you're still one of them.

11
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:30,280
You still think like one of them.

12
00:00:35,070 --> 00:00:37,070
Here folks is the house of Aaron Echolls.

13
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:43,030
Quite a show, huh?

14
00:00:44,493 --> 00:00:45,767
Don't you people have lives?

15
00:00:46,908 --> 00:00:49,145
You don't see me poking around your trailer park, do you?

16
00:00:49,301 --> 00:00:50,755
Hey, uh, uh, are you the son?

17
00:00:52,182 --> 00:00:55,265
I'm the guy telling you to get back on the bus and get out of my driveway.

18
00:00:55,750 --> 00:00:58,285
Logan! Come back in the house, honey.

19
00:01:08,605 --> 00:01:10,312
Hey, you guys are out early.

20
00:01:11,537 --> 00:01:12,053
Here.

21
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:17,665
Hey Logan. Come here.

22
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,370
Get a few shots with my son, huh?

23
00:01:23,588 --> 00:01:24,360
There you go.

24
00:01:24,511 --> 00:01:25,938
Smile, Logan.

25
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,509
Don't forget these folks pay for all of this, huh?

26
00:01:33,139 --> 00:01:33,956
Thanks, Dad.

27
00:01:34,151 --> 00:01:37,833
You know I polled the rest of the soccer team? None of them want to see my junk.

28
00:01:38,022 --> 00:01:39,501
Well, now you're covered.

29
00:01:40,399 --> 00:01:43,772
Oh, you didn't tell me that elections were this week. You should run.

30
00:01:44,185 --> 00:01:48,205
I think it would be a very impressive line on your college applications.

31
00:01:48,282 --> 00:01:52,000
Please Dad. All they do is sell candy and argue about prom decorations.

32
00:01:52,066 --> 00:01:53,407
Right, that's all they do now.

33
00:01:54,027 --> 00:01:55,364
Until the reign of Kane.

34
00:01:56,542 --> 00:02:00,197
Dear god! May no one have just heard him say reign of Kane.

35
00:02:01,313 --> 00:02:04,651
So, my dad wants to take me to the San Diego Zoo this weekend.

36
00:02:04,785 --> 00:02:06,371
Aw, man, I love the zoo.

37
00:02:06,738 --> 00:02:09,182
Everyone gets all excited about the monkey house.

38
00:02:09,505 --> 00:02:11,046
I'm a big cat man myself.

39
00:02:11,119 --> 00:02:13,790
My dad's gone a little nutty with all these father-daughter days.

40
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:15,531
Yeah, see me on the other hand,

41
00:02:15,721 --> 00:02:17,743
would love to go to the zoo with my dad.

42
00:02:18,378 --> 00:02:20,657
- Wallace, don't… 
- But he's dead, so.

43
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:23,948
Okay. I hate myself. Are you happy?

44
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:30,876
Yo! Man! Over here.

45
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,432
Keep the change.

46
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:39,293
You're not allowed delivery.

47
00:02:39,423 --> 00:02:41,633
And you're not allowed to breathe my air.

48
00:02:41,716 --> 00:02:44,906
Go. Shoo. Return to Xanadu.

49
00:02:50,309 --> 00:02:52,650
Wanda Varner just had her food delivered.

50
00:02:52,729 --> 00:02:54,802
And that's wrong how?

51
00:02:54,872 --> 00:02:57,354
She doesn't have any Pirate Points.

52
00:02:57,472 --> 00:03:00,874
Oh, I see. You're new.

53
00:03:01,971 --> 00:03:02,665
I am.

54
00:03:02,754 --> 00:03:06,260
Pirate points are earned by being a contributing member of the school.

55
00:03:06,379 --> 00:03:09,363
You get them for being in student council, for sports…

56
00:03:09,425 --> 00:03:09,993
Cheerleading?

57
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:11,447
Is a sport.

58
00:03:13,245 --> 00:03:14,810
Oh, Mr Clemmons!

59
00:03:17,167 --> 00:03:20,659
Mr Clemmons. Wanda Varner ordered in Chinese food.

60
00:03:26,788 --> 00:03:28,677
Wanda, I know you know the rules.

61
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:31,334
If you'd like the privilege of having your lunch delivered,

62
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:33,705
why don't you get more involved here at Neptune.

63
